<h2><a name="getc" id="getc">getc</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Składnia:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> getc<span class="br0">&#40;</span> FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>stream <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>

Funkcja getc() zwraca kolejny znak pobrany ze strumienia, lub <em><acronym title="End of file">EOF</acronym></em> w przypadku osiągnięcia końca pliku. Funkcja getc() jest identyczna z funkcją fgetc(). Poniższy, przykładowy kod:

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="kw4">int</span> ch<span class="sy0">;</span>
    FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>input <span class="sy0">=</span> fopen<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;plik.txt&quot;</span><span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="st0">&quot;r&quot;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
&nbsp;
    ch <span class="sy0">=</span> getc<span class="br0">&#40;</span> input <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
    <span class="kw1">while</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> ch <span class="sy0">!=</span> EOF <span class="br0">&#41;</span>
    <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
        <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/printf.html"><span class="kw3">printf</span></a><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;%c&quot;</span><span class="sy0">,</span> ch <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
        ch <span class="sy0">=</span> getc<span class="br0">&#40;</span> input <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span>
    <span class="br0">&#125;</span></pre>
<p>

wypisuje zawartość pliku na standardowe wyjście.
</p>

<p>
